Enable breakpoints ( 

				../../../../../images/eiffelstudio/icons/16x16/breakpoints_enable_icon.png
			 ), disable breakpoints ( 

				../../../../../images/eiffelstudio/icons/16x16/breakpoints_disable_icon.png
			 ) and remove breakpoints ( 

				../../../../../images/eiffelstudio/icons/16x16/breakpoints_delete_icon.png
			 ) have all global and local actions. Left-clicking on them has a global action: all set breakpoints of the system will be respectively enabled, disabled, or discarded. However, it is also possible to 

				../../../../../tools/eiffelstudio/reference/05_general_interface_description/10_general_interface_mechanisms/10_pick_and_drop.xml
				drop
			 a feature or a class onto them, in which case only set breakpoints of the feature/class will be affected.
